{"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/forge\/xcodepreviewsupport"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Forge"}],"title":"Xcode Preview Support"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/XcodePreviewSupport","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Architecture and Best Practices","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ModularArchitecture","doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SOLIDPrinciples"],"anchor":"Architecture-and-Best-Practices","generated":true}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide preview-safe mock factories that activate automatically in Xcode Previews."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Dependencies that hit the network, access the file system, or perform heavy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"computation are problematic in Xcode Previews. Forge lets you provide a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preview"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"factory that is used automatically when running inside a preview — no conditional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"checks needed in your view code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"The preview Parameter","anchor":"The-preview-Parameter","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preview"},{"type":"text","text":" closure to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/provide(_:key:_:preview:)"},{"type":"text","text":" alongside the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"normal factory:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["public var authService: any AuthServiceProtocol {","    provide(.singleton) {","        AuthService(network: self.networkClient)","    } preview: {","        MockAuthService()","    }","}","","public var networkClient: any NetworkClientProtocol {","    provide(.singleton) {","        URLSessionNetworkClient()","    } preview: {","        MockNetworkClient()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When the code runs inside an Xcode Preview, ","type":"text"},{"code":"MockAuthService()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is returned. In","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"production, ","type":"text"},{"code":"AuthService(network:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How Preview Detection Works","anchor":"How-Preview-Detection-Works","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Forge detects the preview environment by checking for the "},{"code":"XCODE_RUNNING_FOR_PREVIEWS","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"environment variable, which Xcode sets to "},{"code":"\"1\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when rendering previews. This is the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"standard detection mechanism used across the Swift community."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Resolution Precedence","anchor":"Resolution-Precedence","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/provide(_:key:_:preview:)"},{"type":"text","text":" is called, resolution follows this order:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Overrides"}]},{"text":" — always checked first (test overrides take priority)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Preview factory"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — used if running in a preview and a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preview"},{"type":"text","text":" closure was provided"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Normal factory","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — the default production path"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"text":"Preview Values Are Never Cached","anchor":"Preview-Values-Are-Never-Cached","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Preview factories are called fresh on every resolution, regardless of the declared","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Scope","type":"reference"},{"text":". Even if a dependency is registered as ","type":"text"},{"code":".singleton","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the preview factory","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"runs every time in a preview context. This ensures previews always reflect the latest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"mock state.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"When to Provide a Preview Factory","anchor":"When-to-Provide-a-Preview-Factory","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide one for:"}]}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Network clients and API services"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Database and file system access"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Analytics and logging services"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any dependency that performs I\/O or has side effects"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Skip it for:"}]}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pure in-memory services (formatters, validators, parsers)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Simple value types or data transformations","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Dependencies that already work correctly without network access"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Multiple Preview Variants","anchor":"Multiple-Preview-Variants","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use different overrides within "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#Preview"},{"type":"text","text":" blocks to show different states:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["#Preview(\"Logged In\") {","    AuthContainer.shared.override(\\.authService) {","        MockAuthService(isLoggedIn: true)","    }","    return ProfileView()","}","","#Preview(\"Logged Out\") {","    AuthContainer.shared.override(\\.authService) {","        MockAuthService(isLoggedIn: false)","    }","    return ProfileView()","}","","#Preview(\"Error State\") {","    AuthContainer.shared.override(\\.authService) {","        MockAuthService(shouldFail: true)","    }","    return ProfileView()","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This lets you preview the same view in multiple states without changing any production","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"code.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Testing-Preview-Behavior","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Testing Preview Behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The framework includes an internal "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_isPreviewOverride"},{"type":"text","text":" property (accessible via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@testable import"},{"type":"text","text":") that lets tests simulate the preview environment:"}]},{"code":["@testable import Forge","","PreviewContext._isPreviewOverride = true","defer { Pr